-- Russia-China Fund Seeks Further $2 Billion, Dmitriev Says
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2012-04-29T07:40:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/russia-china-fund-seeks-further-2-billion-dmitriev-says.html
A joint investment fund will be set
up by China and  Russia  by the end of June, according to Kirill Dmitriev, chief executive officer of the Russian Direct
Investment Fund.  The fund will have $1 billion in capital from each country
and is seeking a further $2 billion from Chinese institutional
investors, Dmitriev said in a statement yesterday. As much as 70
percent will be invested in Russia and the  Commonwealth of
Independent States , he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in Moscow at 
